cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for road-user importance estimation using computer vision techniques and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with decision-making for self-driving cars and driver assistance systems, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed architecture involves exploiting the local and global context of the scene, which is a common theme in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new dataset of real-world driving, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the safety and security of self-driving cars, which could be relevant to researchers in the field of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
